CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 25, 1956, pg. A38, reads: " Didn't Make It - It looks like petite Imogene Carter needs a stepladder to light Raymond Harris' cigarette, because adding her arm to her five foot, on-inch height is not enough to reach the seven foot, seven-inch skyscraper wine promoter. A Philadelphian who formerly played basketball for the famed Renaissance, Raymond paused in Pittsburgh and encountered the tiny Miss Carter. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Raymond Harris wearing tuxedo, holding bottle of Hi-Boy wine, and standing in front of Hi-Boy sign
